cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.EM

Reasoning: 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper presents a new technique for dynamic power management in neuromorphic many core systems, which can be considered an emerging technology in the field of computer science.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper describes the implementation of a test chip in 28 nm SLP CMOS technology, which includes 4 processing elements (PE) and employs a fast dynamic voltage and frequency scaling (DVFS) technique for power management.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper focuses on neuromorphic simulation software and benchmarks, which are related to neural computing.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper presents a power management architecture for a many core system, which can be considered a control system.
- cs.EM (Embedded Systems): The paper describes the implementation of a test chip in CMOS technology, which can be considered an embedded system.
